cs.IR, cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.DB 

Reasoning: The paper deals with improving the efficiency of information retrieval systems by incorporating human-and-society level knowledge in the queries using Wikipedia semantics. This involves the use of intelligent algorithms and evolutionary procedures for automated query learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.IR (Information Retrieval). The paper also involves natural language processing and machine learning techniques, which are covered in sub-categories cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The use of evolutionary procedures falls under sub-category cs.LG (Machine Learning) and the incorporation of Wikipedia semantics involves database management, which is covered in sub-category cs.DB (Databases).
